<font face="Arial" size="+2"><center><p><b>Motion of the Planets</b></p></center>
</font><font face="Arial" size="--">
<p>Some of the calculations in this module involve very large numbers. These are often expressed in Standard Form - see CALMAT MoLS Lesson 1-11 
<a href="runcal.htm#==k:\calmat\tcrun.exe calpopup //?~ 0 1 11 a~?">section a</a>. In 
<a href="runcal.htm#==k:\calmat\tcrun.exe calpopup //?~ 0 1 11 d~?">section d</a> Standard Form is defined and the <a href="runcal.htm#==k:\calmat\tcrun.exe calpopup //?~ 0 1 11 e -1~?">tutorials in section e</a> enable you to practise converting normal numbers to Standard Form and vice versa.</p>

<p>Questions <a href="launch.htm#q0882"><b>882 </b></a>and <a href="launch.htm#q0883"><b>883 </b></a>involve converting units which you will need in this part of the course.</p>

